<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Sorry for the late reply. Here goes : <P>If your darkness is resisted, at least you have FD  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"> I have nothing but an 8 (I think) second casting time gate spell, or a pet with a root spell that is resisted way too often because the pet is so many levels lower than what I'm fighting.<P>It seems to me that you're still comparing HPs between necro and mage pets like its a stat to consider when comparing the two pets.  HP is *not* a stat to look at if comparing the two.  That was one of the main points in my post.  As far as I can tell, the only reason why a necro pet would need HP is to absorb damage while the necro is casting a spell, like darkness, fear, or feign death :P.  But a magician's pet needs HP to soak up damage during the ENTIRE battle, since mages don't get any nifty spells like fear or any sort of melee debuffs - not to mention no snare spell.  So please, comparing HP between the two pets is not the thing to do  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>What I was saying mainly applied to higher levels, like 40+.  Just like necros get a fear spell that lasts longer at level 34 (42 seconds instead of 18?)  I would think that mages should get pets that last considerably longer, or do considerably more damage to counterbalance their apparent lack of HP.  This wouldn't make the mage MORE powerful than the necro, since mage pets have COMPLETELY different roles.  You have to understand how much we rely on our pets...and when our pets die too fast for us to put enough nukes in, we're dead not long after since we don't have any escape spells besides a long casting gate spell.  Absor said that that's the way magicians are supposed to be...no form of escape or defense other than our pet.  But what if our pet died to some mob that a necro with a "weaker" pet with less hp can fear kite?  We die. There's no way we could get a gate off with those hard-hitting mobs double attacking the snot out of us. Just what I think as a mage that plays too much EQ.  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">
</FONT>
