<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well I agree with you in some ways, but your pet is much better then the necro. What you could say is that you feel your spells in conjunction with your pet is not up to par with the necro combonation, that I can understand you saying. But please when it comes down to strictly pets the mage is better hands down not to mention the damage shields the summoned weapons the healing and the other buffs you guys can do with you pets.<BR>When it comes to the other factors yes a necro can fd, but again you must realize this is a spell not a monk ability and it does fail. I dont use it outdoors unless the critter summons or is faster then sow.As far as getting gate off, ive gotten it off with 3 mobs hitting me, that would work for all casters.<BR>When my darkness is resisted I have to wait for my pet to taunt it off (if its not a summoner or faster then jboots) when it does I have to recast darkness and hope my pet survives. If I didnt have jboots I have to hope I can get my fd or my gate off, if I go with fd I have to hope it works!<BR>I know that my darkness spells are resisted quite often and probably the same amount as your pets root you just have to run around until your pet taunts it off (root is a great taunt). The only problem is if you dont have jboots or some kind of speed, then your in trouble.<BR>You may not believe it, but alot of the necro safety spells (darkness, fear, fd) are resisted or dont work often, ask necro's. When it comes to soloing out doors the only one better then a necro pre 50 is a druid. When it comes to indoors mage's beat necro's because we cant use fear our pet gets munched and we have to sit there while our dots take forever to take it down.Mages use earth pet to root, nuke nuke nuke.<BR>I do believe that if the root breaks often or doesnt hold long it should be fixed. But its like I said before all classes need some tweeking here or there, but when it comes to the pets, the mage pets are great. Btw the necro fear spell is like your root, it gets resisted and the longest ive had it last was 18sec the shortest was it took affect then wore off at the same time.Necro's also rely on there pets as well, our spells have long casting times and we rely on them to intercept the mob before it gets to us.And the last but not least thing is when it comes to soloing I see mages, wizards,shamans and druids soloing the same places I do.
