Isorashi you have a great resource right here at your finger tips, its called casters realm.I would suggest looking up some of the things you find amazing, you may find that they arent as amazing as you think.<BR>First off Shock of poison is not a dot, it is strictly direct damage.Its damage at 24 is around 145 or so and tops out at lvl 29 at 164 or somewhere around there, not 176.I suggest to reafirm what im saying look this up right on this site.<BR>Second when your grouped with a necro your pet will die first, the reason is your pet does more damage and casts spells therefore causing higher agro. Your pet agro will also increase if you put on damage shields and the summoned weapons which again causes mor damage therefore higher agro.<BR>Now comes the pets! Mage pets do not do much more damage then necro pets, but they do out damage them. The damage is also more intensified when you give them the summoned weapons and I personally would add in the damage shield as part of the pets damage output.<BR>As far as the proc's, the necro pet's proc is a joke and the first time necro pet begins to proc is at 44th and I believe the damage is less then a 20pt lifetap proc.( I may be wrong on the proc damage but its not much higher and could very well be lower).<BR>Here is where the real big difference between the pets are noticed, the HP. There is no real comparison here, the Mage pets have much more hp then there necro counter part, and they very well should have more! Just as an example the lvl 49 necro pet has 2400hp, the lvl 49 mage pet has 3k+.Also at higher lvls your pets for the equal lvl will con blue to you, Im a 56 necro and 20% of my 56 lvl pets con GREEN to me! That will never happen to a mage, and shouldnt happen to necro's either.<BR>As far as pets getting 50% of the exp. getting taken by the pet as unfair, I have to agree with you, expecially for the magician, what is a magician with out his pet.They built the magician to work with his pet and then they impose a 50% penalty, thats just plain stupid!The only saving grace is that if you out do your pets damage you dont take the 50% penalty, but when it comes to the vellious and kunark creatures that gets a little tough.<BR>The last issue is this, ALL Int caster's with the exception of enchanters pretty much suck after 50th lvl. The reason is that the mage's,wizards' and necro's cannot compete with the damage done by the melee classes at these lvls.Sure each of these classes have some minor things they can do (summon water stones, COH, Evac,Mana battery etc.), but overall the usefullness of these classes have been diminished greatly.Now the warriors,monks,Paly,SK and ranger have gear that allow them to breath underwater,gate,hp regen, heal, cast darkness, etc. Yes the int casters can still do things and can do damage but they are not nearly as usefull as the used to be, as the warrior with the fishbone earing and the bracer that can cast darkness how much he needs us when he is clicking on his gate potion!
