Just to clarify a couple things to Mr. Anon.<P>1) A pets damage shield does not increase agro.  The damage done by any damage shield goes to no one. I know because I have casted a damage shield on myself and let a skelie beat himself to death and the corpse dissappeared as soon as it died.<P>2) unless you are talking about duel wield, giving our pets weapons does nothing to thier damage output.... in the sense that at any level we can't summon a weapon that will give the pet more attacking power than it already has.<P>Other than that, there are the ways of escape... I would look on your necro board, I posted something there that another necro agreed with.  I dont remember the title of the dicussion but its one of the new ones.  Anyway, it just states that you have MANY more <I>options</I> to escape than we do.  We basically have two option according to Absor, our gate and our pet  <IMG SRC="rolleyes.gif" border="0"> , which I know no mage considers an escape option.  The whole point people are tring to make is that since we are so lacking in our defense, we should have great offensive skills.  Not so much better nuking capabilities, but definately in our pets.  I'm not saying our pets are weak... far from it, they ARE the best in the game... but they are not good enough for what we have to sacrifice.  Our epic pet should have damage output of at least half of what a monk can do in the same amount of time.  This would be a step in balancing mages to melee classes.  I think they did a great job for wizzies and their new "bane" spells.  Now they just need to work on the other casters.<P>Oh and one more thing... why the hell do druids get a DD that does the same amount as our highest bolt and has a lower casting time?   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Mikhal The Flame<BR>- We Burn... <BR>Dark Elf Mage of Innoruuk<BR>42 levels of summoning mudballs<BR>Bristlebane<P>::8 hours camping quillmane without even seeing her::
