About giving our pets weapons... I know for a fact that since some patch a while ago, weapon delays were taken out of enhancements that pets get when you give them weapons... that is a fact.  The delay of weapons no longer increases the speed in which pets attack (this was due to necros giving thier pets daggers and seeing them do non stop 44's)  Before this patch (I believe) Mages wern't even allowed to give our pets weapons.  Also... That patch (or some later patch) reduced the poccing of items that pets use.  You might be thinking about the SoR (sword of Runes) which procs a 41 damage spell.  Unfortunatley this spell is supposed to be only usable against summoned creatures, which they fixed a little while ago.  As far as damage... A pets max damage at any level is more than that of any summoned weapon we get at that level so giving the pet a weapon does nothing to damage output (except to activate DW before 39, which I think you can do as well).  I hope this clarifies things.  As for the damage shield, I wasn't 100% sure... I just said that because that is what other people have said and that was my experience.<P>Also I would like to know if anyone knows how they get max damage from weapons... say if you have a SoR (dam 7)  whats the max damage you can do?<P>--------------------<P>Mikhal The Flame<BR>- We Burn... <BR>Dark Elf Mage of Innoruuk<BR>42 levels of summoning mudballs<BR>Bristlebane<P>::8 hours camping quillmane without even seeing her::
