I just thought id chime in my two-cents about the magician class.  I have played a magician for 53 levels and have basically retired my character.  Why?  Because our soloing capacity at lev 53 pure and simply sucks.  I used to sit in Burningwoods and try and solo the giants there.  The main problem we mages have?  Downtime.  Oh my god the downtime after killing a forest giant ancient(like a lev 44ish mob hits for up to 120).  Usually my pet would be near death, and at the least at lev 53 It would take 50-60% of my mana to drop the mob.  So id sit there and meditate for about 6mins or so and go and kill another giant.  Id see the necros running up and grabbing another giant every 2 mins or so simply becuase they regenerate their mana back 5 times quicker than us. I meditate,meditate,mediate. If any of you are in the 50's you can understand my frustration with only being able to solo like 8 or 9 mobs an hour.  We magician's anyway you look at are unefficient killers.  Why is this you ask?  You all know why. We are forced to butt heads with our enemies everytime we fight them.  We have to pump DD after DD into mobs before they kill our pets.  Post 50 we are a sad class to try and solo with.  Necros:  Pet, Fear based spells, Darkness spells, extremely mana efficient dots, root, mana regen ect ect.  Druids:  Snare, Roots, mana efficent Dots, Blasts.  Shaman: Roots, pets, massive dots, Blasts, Mana Regen.  Enchanter: Root, Weak Dots, awesome fear line, pets, awesome mana regen, blasts.  I mean I swear we are in the middle of the list when it comes to soloing in the 50s.  Was it not suppose to be us and Necros that were to be the best at soloing?  No way. There are plenty of classes out there that do a better job then we do at soloing and this is really frustrating to me.  Why are we the only pure caster that has no ability to regen mana whatsoever?  I mean we waste huge chunks of mana trying to kill a mob before it kills our pets and us next yet we have no way of increasing our mana regeneration rate??  Im glad they gave the wizards some form of mana regen I really am, but a wizard was never defined as one of the best soloing classes to be, a magician was. So why no self-weak breeze or something like that? To me, its not better pets or better DD's or anything like that that is the problem.  The problem is we have terrible downtime that makes a supposed soloing class very inefficient at soloing.<P>Lev 53 worn out mage.
