<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have a 60 magician and I often play a friends 60 necromancer. Without a question the necromancer is more powerful, but I really would prefer not to debate that since you really can't compare the two.<P>Problems as I see it in the magician that effect balance would be; resists, offensive vs defensive and endgame.<P>Resists:<BR>We all know that rains resist badly (around half the waves resist, 1/3 if debuffed with malosini first). All magician offensive spells have a pretty high resist rate when compared to dots, drains or other high damage newking classes direct damage. They have bad rolls verse resists to start with and since fire and magic are the highest resisted bases overall, magicians cope it sweet. I'd like to see all resists on magician altered and fixed. This comes into play in the endgame also.<P>Offensive vs Defensive:<BR>Magicians get only 2 forms of defense. The pet they currently have up and gate (5secs cast). As you all know, its impossible to get more then a 3second spell off against most of the stuff that gives experience 55+. Magicians also have the lowest hp/ac of all classes self buffed.<P>That means that magicians have the lowest defense of any classes in the game by a long way. That should mean that gain alot of power in offensive or utility/group spells compared to other classes, and this just isnt the case.<P>The only real way to measure the offense of a class would be by their average damage overtime. In a typical group or raid situation, maicians come a distance 6th on average damage; Rogues, Monks, Rangers, Warriors, Necros, Magicians.. If you consider solo, since they don't have manaregen or fear to avoid pet damage, they do around 1/4 what a necromancer can.<P>I honestly think that magicians entire offensive doesn't increase enough post 50. Take just the direct damage magic based spells of magicians;<P>Both casted at level 60 (maximum lvl bonus)<BR>L44-Shock of Swords; 250mana,6sec, 600dmg<BR>L57-Shock of Steel; 275mana, 6sec, 825dmg<P>That is an increase of 0.6 efficiency, and 37.5 dmg/sec more, assuming it never resists which doesnt happen. <P>Endgame:<BR>Can CoH, and stick on fearless pet if they don't dispel. Appart from that almost no direct damage lands due to bad resists.
</FONT>
